 integrity and projecting an image of territorial authority. Yet its negative aftermath is not only frequently glossed over; it also fuels further escalation. With new chapters on the border policies of the Obama, Trump, and Biden administrations, Border Games continues to help readers grasp how the busiest border in the world is also one of the most fortified, and why it plays such a complicated and contentious role in both domestic politics and US-Mexico relations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBorder patrolszMexican-American Border Region. 0aBoundaries. 0aDrug controlzUnited States. 0aIllegal immigrationxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aNoncitizensxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aSmugglingzMexican-American Border Region. 4aCRIMINOLOGY. 4aInternational Studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Immigration.2bisacsh  apolicing the flow of drugs and migrants across the us mexico border, border policing, us mexico border politics, border control, trump border policy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075182608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022 Englishz978311099451308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022z9783110994407oZDB-23-PLW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501765803?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501765803423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501765803/original  a978-3-11-075182-6  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-09938